spans.text: Though now no more thy crested chiefs
the martial pomp no more , That graced its gorgeous festivals of yore
the leader of the gartered line

In life's fresh spring , ever buds the promised prime His thoughts shall mount to virtue's meed sublime : The patriot sire shall catch with sure presage Each liberal omen of his opening age ; Then to thy courts shall lead , with conscious joy , In stripling beauty's bloom the princely boy

many an antique tower , in massy state , In the young champion's musing mind shall raise Vast images of Albion's elder days
Vast images of Albion's elder days
the embattled host in bannered pride
no dangers of the deathful day
that Horror's form , a spectre won
of glorious feats achieved in arms
the broad arch with haughty Cuba's fall , And cloth
bursts to purer day : The mystic round , begirt with bolder peers , On virtue's base its rescued glory rears
